    parentName: "ul"
  }, "Ambassador can be used to offload common client connectivity tasks such as monitoring, logging, routing, and security ", "(", "such as TLS", ")", " in a language agnostic way."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "Anti-corruption layer implements a facade between new and legacy applications, to ensure that the design of a new application is not limited by dependencies on legacy systems."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "Backends for Frontends creates separate backend services for different types of clients, such as desktop and mobile. That way, a single backend service doesn\u2019t need to handle the conflicting requirements of various client types. This pattern can help keep each microservice simple, by separating client-specific concerns."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "Bulkhead isolates critical resources, such as connection pool, memory, and CPU, for each workload or service. By using bulkheads, a single workload ", "(", "or service", ")", " can\u2019t consume all of the resources, starving others. This pattern increases the resiliency of the system by preventing cascading failures caused by one service."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "Gateway Aggregation aggregates requests to multiple individual microservices into a single request, reducing chattiness between consumers and services."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
